      • toNumber

        public static IconValueNumber toNumber(String str)
        Convert string to number. Strings are converted to BigDecimal, or to BigInteger if integer format. If isIntegerPrecision is off, instead converts integers to Long, and if isRealPrecision is off, converts decimal numbers to Double.
        Returns:
        null if string is not a number, or if null input.

      • align

        public static IIconAtom.IconTypes align(IconValue x,
                                        IconValue y)
        Derives the aligned number type of two atoms for use in arithmetic operations. If either is a Float or Double, aligns both to REAL, i.e., a matching Double, to preserve floating point arithmetic. Otherwise if either is a BigDecimal, aligns both to BIGDECIMAL, or to REAL if isRealPrecision is off. Otherwise if either is a BigInteger, aligns both to a BigInteger, or to INTEGER is isIntegerPrecision is off. Otherwise, aligns both to INTEGER. The above matches Groovy math.

        Returned type is: BIG_INTEGER if both are BigInteger, BIG_DECIMAL if both are BigDecimal, INTEGER if both are Integer or Long and should use longValue(), and otherwise DOUBLE if either is Float or Double and should use doubleValue().

        Returns:
        aligned numeric type, or null if either argument is null or not a number.
